1. Syntax
Instead of using id we can use "#" #submitButton {text-align: center; color:red;}, must be unique.
div#sidebar {color:blue}
2. Classa - use "."
3. How web browser reads CCS:
#sidebar div p span {color:red;} -> browser reads css from right to left, span, p, div and at the end id
4. Fonts:
a. font-familly -> p{font-familly: Arial, Verdena, Helvetica;}; // use when not sure wheter some certain font is installed on client machine
b. @font-face -> is used to create your own specific fonts,        
c. font-size -> absolute in "px" or relative in "em" (adjustable to mobile devices) pixels/16=em so 1em=16px
d. text-indent -> making indentation at the beggining of the text
e. Select a style: link, visited, hover, active
    a:hover{color:yellow;}// mouse over link
5. Border
a. border-bottom-color
b. border-color
c. border-image
6. Background
    background-attachment - Sets whether a background image is fixed or scrolls with the rest of the page
    background-color - sets the color
    background-image - sets the background image for an element
    background-position -sets the starting position of a background image
    background-repeat - sets how a background image will be repeated (repeat-y, repeat-x,repeat, no-repeat)
    background-size
    background-clip
7. Positioning
    relative, absoulte
8. Float: left, right, none
    .content {float:right;}
    .sidebar {float:left;}
    .footer {clear: both;}
